 Captain Dineo Sekgotodi, provincial spokesperson for the Hawks, says that they have taken over the investigation. Alberto Nharreluga (46) and his son Ernesto Nharreluga (26) were pulled over on the N4 by members of the Middelburg Flying Squad on Saturday 20 April. Five people were arrested in possession of rhino horn over the Easter weekend. They were travelling towards Middelburg and was stopped between Wonderfontein and the Alzu Petroport. Capt. Sekgotodi said that rhino horn as well as a fire arm and ammunition were found in their possession. Father and son will have to stay behind bars until their bail application next week Tuesday. • Two men and a woman were also arrested for possession of rhino horn in Komatipoort over the Easter weekend.  Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 